  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The following config will not load the require:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    mocha: {\r\n        parallel: false,\r\n        require: [\"ts-node/register/files\", \"test/lib/root-hooks.ts\"]\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou have to use `parallel: true` or the root hooks will not load. Using mocha directly works both in parallel and serial mode.\r\n\r\nI didn't find any info about it being a hardhat limitation, so it looks like a bug.\r\n",
